We've been ordering delivery from Ika for about three years now. I'm a very picky person with sushi, especially when it's delivered. Every time we order, we are satisfied with the quality and freshness. Their pricing is very reasonable, especially considering the large portion sizes of their entrees.  The fish in their sushi is always fresh, and the rice is never the hard texture you can get from sushi rice sometimes. A huge plus for me is their salmon sashimi. The portions are much heartier and well-portioned than other restaurants we've ordered from (sometimes at double the price). Their sashimi is always a great texture - that buttery and smooth texture you want in fresh sashimi.  We recommend Ika to our friends & family in the area all the time. Would 100% recommend to anyone looking for a consistent place to order from!

Per a recent Google review, I initially wanted to eat at Ninja Sushi. It also had more people post reviews than here, so...yeah. Good thing I didn't! We hit up Ika Sushi through Google's Assistant's Reserve a Table option. Upon confirmed, we showed up and noticed that the restaurant was EMPTY. There was NOT A SINGLE table of customers. I quickly realized that this was because everyone does delivery/take out here. They had a table to the side for the delivery person to pick up for the next delivery.  After we all decided what we wanted, we placed our order and did not have to wait very long for our food to arrive. As a party of 10, we ordered udon, don bowls (pork katsu and eel), sashimi, sushi rolls, dinner bento and pretty much half of their appetizers menu.  EVERYTHING was delicious! But a specific comment on their sashimi-- I love it! It's ACTUAL pieces of sashimi, like sashimi sized sashimi, not the thin and short pieces like you get at other locations. I would definitely come back, even if I am the only customer eating there.  And those comments about the staff being rude are false. English is not their first language, so please understand that their vocabulary is kind of limited. If you ordered online, then there may have been an issue with the system. I had a 10/10 experience as a in-store customer.
The food took a bit longer than expected for take-out, but it was worth it. The family enjoyed this meal and they are a hard crowd to please. I will be ordering from here again.

Oh joy, yet another sushi place! I've been to at least six of the others in the neighborhood, and didn't expect anything out of the ordinary. I'm glad to have been proven wrong! The first time I was there, I got a tuna roll, a salmon skin roll, a couple pieces of Uni (sea urchin), Tobiko (Flying fish roe) and Ikura (Salmon roe). The tuna was blood red with a good clean taste as a good tuna should be. The Ikura and Tobiko were beautifully fresh too, but the Uni...wow! The Uni was creamy and briny but it didn't have that nasty iodine-y taste that some Uni has. It made me wish that I had ordered more! The next time I went back, I opted for a tuna hand roll that was very generous with the tuna and as fresh as the tuna I had gotten there two days before. The Uni was also perfect, it wasn't a fluke, speaking of which, that was good too! Even though the 30% off offer is now a thing of the past, I plan on being a regular here because the quality of the sushi is definitely a cut above everyone else in the neighborhood. PS, the staff is super nice too.
